/ Fig.1: #block[
Plot of the region in parameter space #mi(`(a, b)`) allowed by the
inflationary conditions in the text. The solid lines represent those
bounds which do not depend on the scale #mi(`M`) of the phase
transition. The dashed curve correspond to the bounds associated with
the scale #mi(`M=10^{11}`) GeV and the dotted curve to those related to
#mi(`M=10^{16}`) GeV. The allowed region is the one below the curves.
The border #mi(`b=0`) is excluded from it. We have labelled the curves
as follows: QG corresponds to the condition associated to neglecting
quantum gravity effects, #mi(`\Phi`) corresponds to the condition for an
increasing scalar field, RW corresponds to the bound on isotropy and
homogeneity at the time of nucleosynthesis and pN--NS corresponds to the
bounds from post--Newtonian experiments and the nucleosynthesis bound on
#mi(`\omega`).
]
